# .pui is a Para SUPERSET of Svelte 5 — block `derived NAME { … }`,
# `effect { … }`, `|>`, `pure`, etc. are NOT valid TS/Svelte, so
# prettier's parser errors on them (it doesn't run parabunPreprocess).
# .pui style is maintained by the Para toolchain, not prettier. Real
# .svelte files (fixtures) ARE formatted (prettier-plugin-svelte).
#
# EXCEPTION: the demo .pui files under demos/scenarios/ are
# hand-formatted to match what prettier produces on the corresponding
# Cloudscape .tsx side. The "side-by-side demo" promise — same
# formatter settings on both panes — would break otherwise: the React
# files get auto-formatted by prettier (100-col, tabs, single quotes,
# trailing commas), and the Para files have to look the same. When
# you touch one of them, eyeball it against its cloudscape counterpart
# (same scenario id, .cloudscape.tsx). Long type aliases / object
# literals get the multi-line layout; everything else stays inline.
*.pui
src/lib/components

